info.author: Albert Thuswaldner
info.description:
People familiar with Matlab(TM) and its load and save functions will find 
      themselves at home with this small python module, I guess. It makes it 
      possible to save your variables in "workspace" or from within a function 
      to a hdf5 file, and later load them back in again.
info.name: pyhdf5io
info.summary: Python module containing high-level hdf5 load and save functions.
info.html_description:
People familiar with Matlab(TM) and its load and save functions will find
themselves at home with this small python module, I guess. It makes it possible to save your variables in “workspace” or from within a function to a hdf5 file, and later load them back in again.
